#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:260
msgid ""
"Partial unrolling also requires `N >= 2`, a positive counter step, a `<` or "
"`<=` comparison, and a limit that does not change inside the loop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:263
msgid ""
"When an annotated outer loop contains an unannotated inner loop, each outer "
"copy receives an intact clone of that inner loop; the inner loop remains a "
"loop. When both loops are annotated, the compiler handles the inner loop "
"first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:268
msgid ""
"To bound compile time and memory, one annotation may create at most 1,024 "
"body copies, 8,192 cloned basic blocks, and 65,536 cloned operations. A "
"request over one of those limits warns and is not unrolled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:272
msgid ""
"For the complete kernel-author reference, see {ref}`Loop unrolling <loop-"
"unrolling>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:276
msgid "When should you unroll?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:278
msgid "Good candidates are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:280
msgid "small loops with a fixed trip count;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:281
msgid "hot counted loops where branch overhead matters;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:282
msgid ""
"software pipelines whose stage selection becomes constant after unrolling;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:283
msgid ""
"loops where several independent copies expose instruction-level parallelism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:285
msgid ""
"Be cautious when the body is large or already uses many registers. Extra "
"code can increase register pressure, reduce occupancy, or put more pressure "
"on the instruction cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:289
msgid ""
"Choose a factor that matches the structure of the algorithm—often a pipeline "
"depth or another small natural group—and benchmark the result. Removing "
"`#[unroll]` should always remain an easy comparison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:293
msgid "To inspect the pass's analysis, build verbosely:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:295
msgid "cargo oxide build <example> --verbose\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:299
msgid ""
"Verbose mode prints the requested factor and the loop facts the pass found. "
"If a request is skipped, a warning explains why. Loop numbers and analysis "
"fields are internal details and may change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:305
msgid "A home for future transforms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:307
msgid ""
"The `mir-transforms` crate keeps reusable analysis separate from IR mutation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:309
msgid ""
"crates/mir-transforms/src/\n"
"├── analyses/\n"
"│   ├── loop_info.rs      # which blocks belong to each loop?\n"
"│   └── induction.rs      # what are the counter, step, bound, and trip "
"count?\n"
"├── canonicalize.rs       # put supported control flow into a simpler shape\n"
"└── unroll.rs             # prove, clone, reconnect, and clean up loops\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:318
msgid ""
"This separation gives future optimizations a predictable place to live: "
"analyses gather facts, canonicalization normalizes equivalent shapes, and "
"transforms perform behavior-preserving rewrites. `mir-importer/src/pipeline."
"rs` controls when each pass runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:323
msgid ""
"Every transform should follow the same rule as the unroller: prove the "
"rewrite is safe, bound its resource use, and fall back without changing "
"behavior when a program is outside the supported shape."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:327
msgid "The focused test suite runs with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/compiler-optimizations.md:329
msgid "cargo test -p mir-transforms --all-targets\n"
msgstr ""

